Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new method for constructing a data structure, the suffix tree. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the suffix tree is used in data compression and time series analysis. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possibility as the suffix tree is used in text editing and indexing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper mentions bioinformatics applications. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possibility as the paper presents parallel versions of the algorithm for shared-memory, shared-disk, and shared-nothing architectures.
